🔬 The Three “Microbe Layers” in AI

1. Tokens (smallest visible units)
	•	Words/subwords like: "run", "ing", "Pantheon"
	•	Individually simple
	•	But their arrangement → meaning

👉 Like microbes:
	•	tiny
	•	numerous
	•	context-sensitive

⸻

2. Embeddings (hidden state representations)
	•	Each token becomes a vector in high-dimensional space
	•	Encodes relationships (similarity, tone, intent)

👉 This is closer to biochemical signaling:
	•	not visible directly
	•	but strongly influences outcomes

⸻

3. Weights & Attention (interaction rules)
	•	Billions of parameters determining:
	•	what matters
	•	what gets ignored
	•	what patterns activate

👉 This is the ecosystem dynamics:
	•	like microbial competition/cooperation
	•	constantly shaping the “internal environment”

